# BeoSound 5C Services Setup

## Automated Installation (Recommended)

Use the provided scripts for easy service management:

### Install All Services
```bash
sudo ./install-services.sh
```

### Uninstall All Services  
```bash
sudo ./uninstall-services.sh
```

## Manual Installation

Create the service files as per the files in here. All logs are then routed to RAM.

### Register and enable, e.g.,
```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable beo-bluetooth.service
sudo systemctl start beo-bluetooth.service
```

### Control with e.g.,
```bash
sudo systemctl stop beo-bluetooth.service
sudo systemctl start beo-bluetooth.service
sudo systemctl restart beo-bluetooth.service
```

### Check status
```bash
systemctl status beo-bluetooth.service
```

### Tail logs with timestamps
```bash
journalctl -u beo-bluetooth.service -f -l
```

### Tail logs just like they would show in STDOUT
```bash
journalctl -u beo-bluetooth.service -f -o cat
```

## Service Dependencies

- `beo-http.service` - Base HTTP server (port 8000)
- `beo-ui.service` - Chromium UI kiosk (depends on HTTP)
- `beo-media.service` - Media/Sonos server (port 8766)
- `beo-input.service` - Hardware input server (port 8765)
- `beo-bluetooth.service` - Bluetooth remote service
- `beo-masterlink.service` - MasterLink sniffer
